✅ What is Geolocation Testing?
- Geolocation testing verifies application behavior based on user location (latitude & longitude)
- Usef for:
    - Locaiton-based content
    - Currencty / language change
    - Geo-restrictions

✅ How Selenium Handles Geolocation?
- Selenium uses Chrome DevTools Protocol (CDP) to override location.
- Steps to perform:
    - Allow location permission
    - Set latitude & longitude
    - Open applicaition

✅ Example (Chrome – Recommended 🔥)

from selenium import webdriver

options = webdriver.ChromeOptions()

options.add_experimental_option("prefs", {
    "profile.default_content_setting_values.geolocation" : 1
})

driver= webdriver.Chome(options = options)

# Set location (Banglore)
driver.execute_cdp_cmd("Emulation.setGeolocationOverride",{
    "latitude" : 12.9716,
    "longitude" : 77.5946,
    "accuracy" : 100
})

driver.get("https://whatmylocation.com/")

